      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial FEA solver (Ansys Mechanical) used with documented version control, regression test suite, and FDA-recognized software quality assurance plan. Required Gradation 2: documented SQA plan with version control.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 used with full SQA documentation including version control, change management log, and regression testing against benchmark problems. Achieved Gradation 3 due to independent verification of solver outputs against published benchmark solutions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Verification against at least one analytical or benchmark solution relevant to the physics of interest (large-deformation elasto-plastic beam bending). Required Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "FEA code verified against Euler-Bernoulli cantilever beam analytical solution and NAFEMS benchmark LE1 for linear elastic stress. Nonlinear material response verified against published Chaboche plasticity benchmark. All verification errors below 1%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mesh convergence study demonstrating QoI change less than 5% between successive refinement levels. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the screw-rod-vertebral body assembly. Stiffness QoI changed by 3.1% between coarse and medium mesh, and 0.9% between medium and fine mesh. Final mesh selected at medium refinement level; discretization error estimated at 1.8% using Richardson extrapolation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence criteria documented and demonstrated to be below 1e-4 for all load steps. Required Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson nonlinear solver employed with force residual convergence criterion of 1e-5. Energy convergence also monitored. No load steps failed to converge; time-stepping sensitivity confirmed by halving step size with QoI change less than 0.3%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation workflow with independent review of model setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts. Required Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed independently by a second analyst not involved in original model construction. Boundary condition application, contact definitions, and post-processing scripts verified against ASTM F1717 test configuration schematic. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of constitutive model selection and contact formulation relative to observed physical behavior. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity selected for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) based on published coupon test data. Augmented Lagrangian contact formulation used for screw-rod interface. Model form uncertainty quantified by comparison of two constitutive model variants; QoI sensitivity to model form estimated at 2.4%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs sourced from measurements or certified material data sheets with documented uncertainty. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (114 GPa ± 3 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa ± 15 MPa) sourced from ASTM F136 certified material test reports for the specific lot used in bench testing. Screw geometry digitized from CMM measurements of test articles. Input uncertainty propagated through model using a screening sensitivity study that identified elastic modulus and yield strength as dominant contributors to stiffness QoI variability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test articles confirmed to be from the same design family and manufacturing lot as the simulated construct, with dimensional verification. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 test constructs assembled from screws and rods from the same manufacturing lot as the design under assessment. CMM measurements confirmed screw dimensions within 0.05 mm of nominal. Polyaxial screw head torque confirmed per device IFU. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison under ASME V&V 40 guidance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading configurations or a justification is provided for the selected condition. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration only. Torsion and tension-bending modes not tested in this validation activity. Achieved Gradation 2 because only one load condition tested; this is the known below-threshold factor documented in the COU description. Compensating evidence from literature cited but not sufficient to elevate to Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstration that simulation inputs are equivalent to or bounded by the experimental conditions, including fixture compliance and load application geometry. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Load application geometry, fixture compliance, and displacement rate confirmed equivalent between simulation and test. UHMWPE block material properties for vertebral body simulant measured and applied in FEA. Crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min) confirmed quasi-static; inertial effects negligible. Equivalency confirmed for all major input parameters."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for each QoI with pre-specified acceptance bound. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement following ASME V&V 40 Eq. 9. Validation uncertainty uval accounts for input uncertainty, numerical uncertainty, and experimental repeatability. All E/uval values below the pre-specified bound of 1.96. Comparison plots with 95% confidence intervals provided in the validation report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the device performance specification and regulatory submission QoIs. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are primary performance endpoints in the 510(k) submission predicate comparison. Force at 40 mm displacement is the ASTM F1717 failure criterion. All three QoIs are directly specified in the device performance specification and are the same metrics evaluated in the bench test report submitted to FDA."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on the same device design, same material, same loading mode, and same scale as the COU. Required Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on production-equivalent non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs under ASTM F1717 compression-bending — identical to the COU. No geometric scaling, material substitution, or loading mode extrapolation required. The validation activity directly supports the COU with no bridging arguments needed."
    }
